Concept for shapes and colors for all the LEVELS.

Every Pack has 4 LEVELS.  
Note: In each level there are 5 puzzles, so each Pack has 20 puzzles.  But that doesn't matter for this.

We want to have an array of shapes0 and shapes1, "shape sets".  
I may have 15 shape sets, or I may have 30.  We want it to work no matter the amount of shape sets (there is no dependency on pack number or level)
I do want PACK 1 LEVEL 1 to use shape set 0, PACK 1 LEVEL 2 to use shape set 1, until we hit the end of the shapes array, and then we will use a formula for getting shape sets after that.
Also, I do want PACK 1 LEVEL 1 to use color set 0, PACK 1 LEVEL 2 to use color set 1, until we hit the end of the colors array, and then we will use a formula for getting shape sets after that.

IE:
function getLevelAssets(packIndex, levelIndex) {
  const SHAPE_PRIME = 17;
  const COLOR_PRIME = 13;

  // Shapes: walk first, then formula
  const shapeSetIndex = levelIndex < shapeSets.length
    ? levelIndex
    : (packIndex * SHAPE_PRIME + levelIndex) % shapeSets.length;

  // Colors: walk first, then formula
  const colorSetIndex = levelIndex < colors.length
    ? levelIndex
    : (packIndex * COLOR_PRIME + levelIndex) % colors.length;

  const [shape0, shape1] = shapeSets[shapeSetIndex];

  return {
    shape0,
    shape1,
    color0: colors[colorSetIndex][0],
    color1: colors[colorSetIndex][1]
  };
}


We can use this type of array for shapes perhaps
export const shapeSets: [Shape, Shape][] = [
  // Shape Set 0
  [
    {
      id: 'shape0',
      path: 'M91.5 50C91.5 ...'  // Circle
    },
    {
      id: 'shape1',
      path: 'M50 5L95 50L50 95L5 50L50 5Z'  // Diamond
    }
  ],
  // Shape Set 1
  [
    {
      id: 'shape0',
      path: 'M....'  // Car
    },
    {
      id: 'shape1',
      path: 'M....'  // House
    }
  ],
  // Continue...
];



For colors, We may have 8 sets (as an example):

export const colors: [string, string][] = [
  // Color Set 1
  ['#2196F3', '#FFC107'],
  // Color Set 2
  ['#1c8278', '#d81b60'],
  // Color Set 3
  ['#e28e18', '#744596'],
  // Color Set 4
  ['#FF5722', '#4CAF50'],
  // Color Set 5
  ['#9C27B0', '#03A9F4'],
  // Color Set 6
  ['#CDDC39', '#FF9800'],
  // Color Set 7
  ['#795548', '#607D8B'],
  // Color Set 8
  ['#F44336', '#8BC34A']
];
